[[Category:Crew of HMS Bounty| ]]

{{pp-pc1}} {{pp-move-indef}} {{calendar}} {{This date in recent years}} {{Day}}
==Events== * [[303]] &ndash; [[Roman emperor]] [[Diocletian]] orders the destruction of the Christian church in [[Nicomedia]], beginning eight years of [[Diocletianic Persecution]]. * [[532]] &ndash; [[Byzantine emperor]] [[Justinian I]] orders the building of a new [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Orthodox Christian]] [[basilica]] in [[Constantinople]] &ndash; the [[Hagia Sophia]]. *[[1455]] &ndash; Traditional date for the publication of the [[Gutenberg Bible]], the first [[Western culture|Western]] [[book]] printed with [[movable type]]. *[[1554]] &ndash; [[Mapuche]] forces, under the leadership of [[Lautaro]], score a victory over the [[Spanish Empire|Spanish]] at the [[Battle of Marihueñu]] in [[Chile]]. *[[1739]] &ndash; At [[York Castle]], the outlaw [[Dick Turpin]] is identified by his former schoolteacher. Turpin had been using the name Richard Palmer. *[[1778]] &ndash; [[American Revolutionary War]]: [[Friedrich Wilhelm von Steuben|Baron von Steuben]] arrives at [[Valley Forge, Pennsylvania]] to help to train the [[Continental Army]]. *[[1820]] &ndash; [[Cato Street Conspiracy]]: A plot to murder all the British cabinet ministers is exposed. *[[1836]] &ndash; [[Texas Revolution]]: The [[Siege of the Alamo]] (prelude to the [[Battle of the Alamo]]) begins in [[San Antonio, Texas]]. *[[1847]] &ndash; [[Mexican–American War]]: [[Battle of Buena Vista]]: In Mexico, American troops under future president General [[Zachary Taylor]] defeat Mexican General [[Antonio López de Santa Anna]]. *[[1854]] &ndash; The official independence of the [[Orange Free State]] is declared. *[[1861]] &ndash; President-elect [[Abraham Lincoln]] arrives secretly in Washington, D.C., after the thwarting of an alleged [[Baltimore Plot|assassination plot]] in [[Baltimore]], [[Maryland]]. *[[1870]] &ndash; [[Reconstruction Era]]: Post-[[American Civil War|U.S. Civil War]] military control of [[Mississippi]] ends and it is readmitted to the [[Union (American Civil War)|Union]]. *[[1883]] &ndash; [[Alabama]] becomes the first [[U.S. state]] to enact an [[Competition law|anti-trust law]]. *[[1885]] &ndash; [[Sino-French War]]: French Army gains an important victory in the [[Battle of Đồng Đăng (1885)|Battle of Đồng Đăng]] in the [[Tonkin]] region of Vietnam. *[[1886]] &ndash; [[Charles Martin Hall]] produced the first samples of man-made [[aluminium]], after several years of intensive work. He was assisted in this project by his older sister, [[Julia Brainerd Hall]]. *[[1887]] &ndash; The [[French Riviera]] is hit by a large earthquake, killing around 2,000. *[[1898]] &ndash; [[Émile Zola]] is imprisoned in France after writing ''[[J'Accuse…!]]'', a letter accusing the French government of [[antisemitism]] and wrongfully imprisoning [[Captain (OF-2)|Captain]] [[Alfred Dreyfus]]. *[[1900]] &ndash; [[Second Boer War]]: During the [[Battle of the Tugela Heights]], the first British attempt to take Hart's Hill fails. *[[1903]] &ndash; [[Cuba]] leases [[Guantanamo Bay Naval Base|Guantánamo Bay]] to the United States "in perpetuity". *[[1905]] &ndash; Chicago attorney [[Paul P. Harris|Paul Harris]] and three other businessmen meet for lunch to form the [[Rotary Club]], the world's first [[service club]]. *[[1909]] &ndash; The [[AEA Silver Dart]] makes the first powered flight in Canada and the [[British Empire]]. *[[1917]] &ndash; First demonstrations in [[Saint Petersburg]], Russia. The beginning of the [[February Revolution]] (March 8 in the [[Gregorian calendar]]). *[[1927]] &ndash; U.S. President [[Calvin Coolidge]] signs a bill by [[United States Congress|Congress]] establishing the [[Federal Radio Commission]] (later replaced by the [[Federal Communications Commission]]) which was to regulate the use of radio frequencies in the United States. * 1927 &ndash; German [[theoretical physics|theoretical physicist]] [[Werner Heisenberg]] writes a letter to fellow physicist [[Wolfgang Pauli]], in which he describes his [[uncertainty principle]] for the first time. *[[1934]] &ndash; [[Leopold III of Belgium|Leopold III]] becomes King of [[Belgium]]. *[[1941]] &ndash; [[Plutonium]] is first produced and isolated by Dr. [[Glenn T. Seaborg]]. *[[1942]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Empire of Japan|Japanese]] submarines [[Bombardment of Ellwood|fire artillery shells]] at the coastline near [[Santa Barbara, California]]. *[[1943]] &ndash; A fire breaks out at Saint Joseph's Orphanage, [[County Cavan]], Ireland, killing 35 children and one adult. * 1943 &ndash; [[Greek Resistance]]: The [[United Panhellenic Organization of Youth]] is founded in Greece. *[[1944]] &ndash; The [[Soviet Union]] begins the [[Operation Lentil (Caucasus)|forced deportation]] of the [[Chechens|Chechen]] and [[Ingush people]] from the [[North Caucasus]] to Central Asia. *[[1945]] &ndash; World War II: During the [[Battle of Iwo Jima]], a group of [[United States Marine]]s and a U.S. Navy [[hospital corpsman]] reach the top of [[Mount Suribachi]] on the island and are [[Raising the Flag on Iwo Jima|photographed raising the American flag]]. * 1945 &ndash; World War II: The [[11th Airborne Division (United States)|11th Airborne Division]], with [[Filipinos|Filipino]] guerrillas, free the captives of the [[Los Baños, Laguna|Los Baños]] internment camp. * 1945 &ndash; World War II: The capital of the [[Philippines]], [[Manila]], is liberated by combined Filipino and American forces. * 1945 &ndash; World War II: Capitulation of [[Nazi Germany|German]] garrison in [[Poznań]]. The city is liberated by [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] and [[History of Poland (1939–45)|Polish]] forces. * 1945 &ndash; World War II: The German town of [[Pforzheim]] is [[Bombing of Pforzheim in World War II|annihilated]] in a raid by 379 British bombers. *[[1947]] &ndash; [[International Organization for Standardization]] is founded. *[[1954]] &ndash; The first mass inoculation of children against [[Poliomyelitis|polio]] with the [[Jonas Salk|Salk]] [[vaccine]] begins in [[Pittsburgh]]. *[[1966]] &ndash; In [[Syria]], [[Ba'ath Party]] member [[Salah Jadid]] leads an intra-party military [[coup]] that replaces the previous government of General [[Amin al-Hafiz]], also a Baathist. *[[1974]] &ndash; The [[Symbionese Liberation Army]] demands $4 million more to release kidnap victim [[Patty Hearst]]. *[[1980]] &ndash; [[Iran hostage crisis]]: [[Supreme Leader of Iran|Supreme Leader]] [[Ayatollah]] [[Ruhollah Khomeini]] states that Iran's parliament will decide the fate of the American embassy hostages. *[[1981]] &ndash; In Spain, [[Antonio Tejero]] attempts [[23-F|a coup d'état]] by capturing the [[Congress of Deputies (Spain)|Spanish Congress of Deputies]]. *[[1983]] &ndash; The [[United States Environmental Protection Agency]] announces its intent to buy out and evacuate the [[Polychlorinated dibenzodioxins|dioxin]]-contaminated community of [[Times Beach, Missouri]]. *[[1987]] &ndash; [[Supernova 1987a]] is seen in the [[Large Magellanic Cloud]]. * 1991 &ndash; In [[Thailand]], General [[Sunthorn Kongsompong]] leads a bloodless [[coup d'état]], deposing Prime Minister [[Chatichai Choonhavan]]. *[[1998]] &ndash; In the United States, [[1998 Kissimmee tornado outbreak|tornadoes in central Florida]] destroy or damage 2,600 structures and kill 42 people. *[[1999]] &ndash; [[Kurds|Kurdish]] rebel leader [[Abdullah Öcalan]] is charged with [[treason]] in [[Ankara]], Turkey. *[[2007]] &ndash; A [[Grayrigg derailment|train derails]] on an evening express service near [[Grayrigg]], [[Cumbria]], England, killing one person and injuring 88. This results in hundreds of points being checked over the UK after a few similar accidents. *[[2008]] &ndash; A [[United States Air Force]] [[B-2 Spirit]] bomber [[2008 Andersen Air Force Base B-2 accident|crashes on Guam]], marking the first operational loss of a B-2. *[[2010]] &ndash; Unknown criminals pour more than 2{{frac|1|2}} million liters of [[diesel oil]] and other [[hydrocarbon]]s into the river [[Lambro]], in northern Italy, sparking an [[environmental disaster]]. *[[2012]] &ndash; A [[23 February 2012 Iraq attacks|series of attacks]] across [[Iraq]] leave at least 83 killed and more than 250 injured. *[[2017]] &ndash; The Turkish-backed [[Free Syrian Army]] [[Battle of al-Bab|captures Al-Bab]] from [[ISIL]].
