{{Infobox recurring event | name = <!--Uses page name if omitted--> | native_name = | native_name_lang = | logo = Belleville_National_Strawberry_Festival_Logo.png | logo_alt = | logo_caption = “A weekend of fun for everyone!” | logo_size = | image = File:Belleville National Strawberry Festival - Main Street from Ferris Wheel.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Main Street from the Ferris wheel | status = <!-- e.g. defunct, active, inactive ... --> | genre = Festival | date = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} "dates=" also works, but do not use both --> | begins = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} --> | ends = <!-- {{end date|YYYY|mm|dd}} --> | frequency = Annually, Father's Day Weekend | venue = Main Street, St. Anthony Catholic Church, Belleville Presbyterian Church, Trinity Episcopal Church, and Victory Park<ref>{{cite news |last=Otzman |first=Rosemary K. |date=June 15, 2017 |title=Belleville National Strawberry Festival welcomes you to town |url=http://bellevilleareaindependent.com/belleville-national-strawberry-festival-welcomes-you-to-town/ |work=Belleville-Area Independent |location=[[Belleville, Michigan]] |access-date=June 16, 2017 }}</ref> | location = [[Belleville, Michigan]] | coordinates = {{coord|42.207144|-83.488502|type:event|display=inline,title}} | country = United States | years_active = <!-- {{age|YYYY|mm|dd}} Date of the first occurrence --> | first = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} "founded=" and "established=" also work --> | founder_name = <!-- or | founders = --> | last = <!-- Date of most recent event; if the event will not be held again, use {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | prev = | next = | participants = | attendance = 200,000 | capacity = | area = | budget = | activity = | leader_name = | patron = | organised = <!-- "organized=" also works --> | filing = | people = | member = | sponsors = [[Meijer]], [[21st Century Newspapers|Heritage Newspapers]] | website = {{url|nationalstrawberryfest.com}} | footnotes = }}
The '''National Strawberry Festival''' in [[Belleville, Michigan]] began as a way for local farmers to celebrate their [[strawberry]] crops.<ref>{{cite news |last=Otzman |first=Rosemary K. |date=June 15, 2017 |title=It’s Strawberry Festival time in Belleville |url=http://bellevilleareaindependent.com/editorial-its-strawberry-festival-time-in-belleville/ |work=Belleville-Area Independent |location=[[Belleville, Michigan]] |access-date=June 16, 2017 }}</ref> Taking place over three days, held the third weekend in June, the festival offers many events for people of all ages.<ref>{{cite news |last=Smith |first=Kyla |date= June 17, 2016 |title=Fest in Belleville has strawberries at tart |url=http://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/local/wayne-county/2016/06/17/fest-belleville-strawberries-tart/86037772/ |newspaper=[[The Detroit News]] |location= [[Detroit]] |access-date= June 18, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Selasky |first=Susan |date= June 18, 2015 |title=Celebrate strawberries this weekend in Belleville |url=http://www.freep.com/story/life/2015/06/18/strawberries-belleville-festival-u-pick/28940481/ |newspaper=[[The Detroit Free Press]] |location= [[Detroit]] |access-date= June 18, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Lee |first=Ardelia |date= June 18, 2015 |title=Don’t Miss It: National Strawberry Festival in Belleville |url=http://www.dailydetroit.com/2015/06/17/dont-miss-it-national-strawberry-festival-in-belleville/ |newspaper=Daily Detroit |location= [[Detroit]] |access-date= Jun 17, 2015}}</ref> In collaboration with area churches and schools, some of the events include: [[File:Strawberry Shortcake from Myrtle Lodge No. 89, F&AM.jpg|thumb|left|Strawberry Shortcake from Myrtle Lodge No. 89, [[Freemasonry|F&AM]]]] * [[Bingo (US)|Bingo]] * Strawberry desserts * Parade * Car show * "Strawberry Queen Pageant" * Live entertainment
Each year the festival attracts over 200,000 people from Southeastern [[Michigan]] and farther.
