{{Infobox NFL game | type = sb | name = LVIII | full name = | image = File:Saints Stadium (3927508936).jpg | caption = | visitor = | visitor_abbr = | visitor_conf = | visitor_place = | home = | home_abbr = | home_conf = | home_place = | visitor_qtr1 = | visitor_qtr2 = | visitor_qtr3 = | visitor_qtr4 = | home_qtr1 = | home_qtr2 = | home_qtr3 = | home_qtr4 = | date = February 4, 2024 | stadium = [[Mercedes-Benz Superdome]] | city = [[New Orleans, Louisiana]] | attendance = | odds = | MVP = | anthem = | coin_toss = | refreee = | HOFers = | halftime = | network = [[NBC Sunday Night Football|NBC]] | announcers = | rating = | share = | commercial = | radio = | radioannouncers = | last = LVII | next = LIX }}
'''Super Bowl LVIII''', the 58th [[Super Bowl]] and the 54th [[AFL–NFL merger|modern-era]] [[National Football League]] (NFL) championship game, will decide the league champion for the 2023 NFL season. The game is scheduled to be played on February 4, 2024 at [[Mercedes-Benz Superdome]] in [[New Orleans, Louisiana]] (with the exact date pending potential changes to the NFL calendar). It will be the eleventh Super Bowl hosted by New Orleans, with the last one being [[Super Bowl XLVII]] in 2013 eleven years earlier, also held at the Superdome.<ref name="sb58sitechosen">{{cite web|last1=Teope|first1=Herbie|title=Arizona, New Orleans chosen as Super Bowl hosts|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000933935/article/arizona-new-orleans-chosen-as-super-bowl-hosts|publisher=NFL.com|accessdate=May 23, 2018}}</ref>
==Host-selection process== Super Bowl LVIII, along with [[Super Bowl LVII]], was part of a new awarding process implemented by the league. In the previous process, cities that wished to host a Super Bowl submitted bids, which were deliberated and voted upon at the league owners' meetings. The new process no longer allows cities to bid for the game; the league now chooses the potential candidates. On May 23, 2018, the league selected New Orleans as the site for Super Bowl LVIII.<ref name="sb58sitechosen"/>
== Broadcasting == Super Bowl LVIII will be broadcast by a network yet to be announced. It will be the first game in the league's next [[NFL on television|television contract]]. If the current rotation continues in the next contract, the game will be televised by [[NBC Sunday Night Football|NBC]].
