{{Infobox pro wrestling championship | championshipname=''Torneo Sangre Nueva'' | image = LuchaLibreObrera062.JPG | image_size =200px | caption = [[Taurus (wrestler)|Taurus]], finalist in the 2013 ''Sangre Nueva'' tournament | currentholder=[[Soberano Jr.]] | won={{dts|2013|3|12}} | promotion=[[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] | created={{dts|2012|3|20}} | mostreigns= | firstchamp=[[Místico II|Dragon Lee]] | oldest=[[El Cholo]] {{nobr|(40 years, 56 days)}} (Competitor) | youngest=[[Soberano Jr.]] {{nobr|(18 years, 206 days)}} | heaviest=[[Bronco (wrestler)|Bronco]] ({{convert|103|kg|lb|abbr=on}}) (Competitor)<!--In Mexico they measure weight in kilograms so that should be first --> | lightest=Soberano Jr. ({{convert|75|kg|lb|abbr=on}})<!--In Mexico they measure weight in kilograms so that should be first --> }} '''''Torneo Sangre Nueva''''' ("The New Blood Tournament") is a [[professional wrestling]] tournament promoted by the Mexican [[lucha libre]] promotion [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] (CMLL), first held in 2012. The tournament focuses primarily on younger wrestlers or wrestlers who work in the lower ranks of the promotion, generally the first or second match of the show, as a way to highlight or promote a wrestler up to a higher level of competition. A total of 27 individuals have competed in the two ''Sangre Nueva'' tournaments held as of 2014 with nine competitors participating in both tournaments held so far: [[Bobby Zavala]], [[Camaleón]], [[El Cholo]], [[Disturbio]], [[Hombre Bala Jr.]], [[Robin (wrestler)|Robin]], [[Soberano Jr.]], [[Stigma (luchador)|Stigma]] and [[Super Halcón Jr.]]. Soberano Jr. is both the youngest competitor over-all (18 years and 206 days old) and the youngest tournament winner as well (19 days and 198 days old), while Cholo is the oldest (40 years and 56 days) at the time of his second tournament participation. Soberano Jr. was the lightest competitor and champion at {{convert|75|kg|lb|abbr=on}} while [[Bronco (wrestler)|Bronco]], at {{convert|103|kg|lb|abbr=on}}, was the heaviest of any tournament competitor so far.
