==Torneo Sangre Nueva 2012== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=''Torneo Sangre Nueva'' (2012) |image= |caption= |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=March 20, 2012 |attendance= |venue=[[Arena Mexico]] |city = [[Mexico City|Mexico City, Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=''[[Homenaje a Dos Leyendas (2012)|Homenaje a Dos Leyendas]]'' (2012) |nextevent=''[[Gran Alternativa 2012|Torneo Gran Alternativa]]'' (2012) |event=''Torneo Gran Alternativa'' |lastevent2=First |nextevent2=''[[#Torneo Sangre Nueva 2013|Torneo Sangre Nueva]]'' (2013) }} The first ever '''''Torneo Sangre Nueva''''' took place in March 2012. Some of the competitors did not fit the "New Blood" tournaments, but in the case of wrestlers like [[Cancerbero]] and [[Raziel (wrestler)|Raziel]], the [[ring name|ring persona]] he portrayed had only been used for around 2 years, making the character a rookie, but not the man under the mask. CMLL has a history of not openly promoting the fact that some of their workers have worked under different identities previously.<ref name=Mondo>{{cite book|author=Madigan, Dan|title=Mondo Lucha A Go-Go: the bizarre & honorable world of wild Mexican wrestling|publisher= HarperColins Publisher|year=2007|chapter=Okay... what is Lucha Libre?|pages=29–40|isbn=978-0-06-085583-3}}</ref> The tournament played out from March 6, 2012, until March 20, 2012, on CMLL's Tuesday shows in Arena Mexico. The first two shows had 8 wrestlers compete for a shot at the finals. Each night the eight wrestlers competed in a "Seeding" battle royal to determine the four on four ''Torneo cibernetico'' elimination match. On the first night [[El Cholo]], [[Soberano Jr.]], [[Cancerbero]], and [[Místico II|Dragon Lee]] comprised one team while [[Bobby Zavala]], [[Titán (wrestler)|Titán]], [[Stigma (luchador)|Stigma]] and [[Camaleón]] on the other. Dragon Lee won the match, lastly eliminating Titán to win the match.<ref name=SangreNuevaA>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediotiempo.com/mas-deportes/lucha-libre/noticias/2012/03/07/se-mantiene-el-reinado-de-la-atlantida|title=Se mantiene el reinado de la Atlantida|date=March 7, 2012|accessdate=October 20, 2012|work=Medio Tiempo|language=Spanish}}</ref> The second block, on March 13, 2012 saw [[Disturbio]], [[Hombre Bala Jr.]], Raziel, and [[Tritón (wrestler)|Tritón]] team up to face [[Robin (wrestler)|Robin]], [[Bronco (wrestler)|Bronco]], [[Hijo del Signo]], and [[Super Halcón Jr.]] Raziel took the victory, eliminating Tritón to end the nearly 25 minute long match to move on to the finals.<ref name=SangreNuevaB>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediotiempo.com/mas-deportes/lucha-libre/noticias/2012/03/14/raziel-a-la-final-de-sangre-nueva|title=Raziel a la Final de Sangre Nueva|date=March 14, 2012|accessdate=October 20, 2012|work=Medio Tiempo|language=Spanish}}</ref> A week later, on March 20, 2012 Dragon Lee and Raziel faced off in the only three fall match of the night. Dragon Lee defeated Raziel to win the ''Torneo Sangre Nueva''.<ref name=SangreNuevaFinals2012>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediotiempo.com/mas-deportes/lucha-libre/noticias/2012/03/21/contento-dargon-lee-por-su-primer-trofeo|title=Contento Dargon Lee por su primer trofeo|date=March 21, 2012|accessdate=October 20, 2012|work=Medio Tiempo|language=Spanish}}</ref>
