;Aftermath On June 20, 2012, CMLL held a press conference, during which ''lucha libre'' priest [[Fray Tormenta]] announced that since Dragon Lee had impressed him with his in ring performance, Fray Tormenta wanted Dragon Lee to take over the role of [[Místico]], his storyline protégé.<ref name=CMLLMisticoII>{{cite web|url=http://cmll.com/noticias.htm|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/68aE9QvBg|title=Místico con alma de Dragón.... ¡Las Amazonas del ring en jaula!|publisher=[[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]]|date=June 21, 2012|archivedate=June 21, 2012|accessdate=June 21, 2012|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=WVMisticoII>{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/viewnews.php?id=1340476258|title=Viva La Raza! Lucha Weekly|date=June 23, 2012|accessdate=June 23, 2012|last=Boutwell|first=Josh|publisher=WrestleView}}</ref> Lee immediately accepted Tormenta's offer and received his new mask to officially become the second incarnation of Místico, taking over the highly successful role following the character's original performer, who had signed with [[WWE]] in January 2011.<ref name=CMLLMisticoII/><ref name=WVMisticoII/><ref name=DragonLeeIsMisticoII>{{cite web|url=http://superluchas.net/2012/06/20/dragon-lee-se-convierte-en-mistico/|title=Dragon Lee se convierte en "Místico"|date=June 20, 2012|accessdate=June 20, 2012|last=Mexicool|first=Rey|work=SuperLuchas|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://superluchas.net/2012/06/20/dragon-lee-es-el-nuevo-mistico/|title=Imagen: Dragón Lee es el nuevo "Místico"|accessdate=June 20, 2012|last=Ruiz Glez|first=Alex|work=SuperLuchas|language=Spanish}}</ref> Titán entered CMLL's ''[[En Busca de un Ídolo]]'' ("In search of an Idol") a few months after narrowly missing out on the ''Sangre Nueva'' tournament finals. The tournament used a point system that allowed fans to vote online, allowing Titán to advance to the second round despite only winning one of his four first round matches.<ref name=Top4>{{cite web|url=http://enbuscadeunidolo.com/resultados.htm|title=Resultados|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BWee6Ik5|archivedate=October 18, 2012|publisher=[[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]]|language=Spanish}}</ref> The fan support propelled Titán to the finale where he defeated Euforia to win the tournament.<ref name=final>{{cite web|url=http://enbuscadeunidolo.com/fotos.htm|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BWeEEfzl|archivedate=October 19, 2012|accessdate=October 19, 2012|title=En Busca de un Idolo 2a Etapa|publisher=[[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]]|language=spanish}}</ref> Titán would later defeat ''En Busca de un Ídolo'' rival [[Pólvora]] to win the [[Mexican National Welterweight Championship]]<ref name=MexWelter>{{cite web|url=http://cmll.com/02_resultados/martes_arena_mex/martes_arenamex.htm|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6ARZ9mFZv|title=Martes 4 de Septiembre del 2012|last=Salazar López|first=Alexis A.|archivedate=September 5, 2012|date=September 5, 2012|accessdate=September 5, 2012|publisher=[[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]]|language=Spanish}}</ref> Cholo, Bobby Zavala, Soberano Jr., Camaleón, Stigma, Robin, Disturbio and Super Halcón Jr. would all compete in the subsequent ''Torneo Sangre Nueva'' in 2013. {{Clear}}
==Torneo Sangre Nueva 2013== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=Torneo Sangre Nueva (2013) |image= |caption= |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=February 26, 2013 |attendance= |venue=[[Arena Mexico]] |city = [[Mexico City|Mexico City, Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=''[[CMLL Torneo Nacional de Parejas Increibles (2013)|Torneo de Parejas Increibles]]'' (2013) |nextevent=''[[Homenaje a Dos Leyendas (2013)|Homenaje a Dos Leyendas]]'' (2013) |event=''Torneo Gran Alternativa'' |lastevent2=''[[#Torneo Sangre Nueva 2012|Torneo Sangre Nueva]]'' (2012) |nextevent2=TBA }} On February 21, 2013, CMLL announced that they were holding another '''''Torneo Sangre Nueva''''' tournament in 2013, possibly making it an annual event. Like the first tournament the 2013 ''Sangre Nueva'' would feature two qualifying ''[[torneo cibernetico]]'' elimination matches with the winner of each facing off in a one-on-one match. In 2013 the ''cibernetico'' match included 10 competitors instead of the eight competitors in the previous year's tournament. The first match took place on February 26, 2013, in [[Arena Mexico]] and saw [[Soberano Jr.]] (son of CMLL wrestler [[Euforia (wrestler)|Euforia]]) outlast [[Camaleón]], [[Stigma (luchador)|Stigma]], [[Horus (wrestler)|Höruz]], [[Hombre Bala Jr.]], [[Akuma (luchador)|Akuma]], [[Espanto Jr. (CMLL)|Espanto Jr.]], [[Herodes Jr.]], [[Cholo (wrestler)|Cholo]] and [[Bobby Zavala]] to qualify for the finals.<ref name=2013BlockA>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediotiempo.com/mas-deportes/lucha-libre/noticias/2013/02/27/soberano-finalista-de-sangre-nueva|title=Soberano, finalista de Sangre Nueva|date=February 27, 2013|accessdate=March 1, 2013|work=Medio Tiempo|language=Spanish}}</ref> During the match Höruz suffered a knee injury as a result of a dive out of the ring, the injury was believed to keep him out of the ring for three months.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://superluchas.net/2013/03/01/horuz-fuera-de-accion/|title=¡Höruz, fuera de acción!|date=March 1, 2013|accessdate=March 1, 2013|work=SuperLuchas|language=Spanish}}</ref> Block B competed on March 5, 2013, for the other finalist spot, with a field that included Genesis, [[Oro Jr.]], [[Robin (wrestler)|Robin]], [[Sensei (wrestler)|Sensei]], [[Super Halcón Jr.]], [[Disturbio]], [[Guerrero Negro Jr.]], [[Inquisidor]], [[Taurus (wrestler)|Taurus]] and [[Zayco]]. As with the 2012 ''Torneo Sangre Nueva'', not everyone competing in the tournament fit the "new blood" description; Sensei had worked for CMLL under that ring persona since 2005 and been a professional wrestler even longer. Inquisidor made his professional wrestling in 1995, but only adopted the Inquisidor name and mask in 2008, with CMLL officially not acknowledging his past history before becoming Inquisidor.<ref name=Luchas2000>{{cite news|title=entrevista con Polvora y Inquisidor|work=Luchas 2000|location=[[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]]|id=issue 583|date=August 15, 2008|language=Spanish}}</ref> The second Cibernetico was won by Taurus, son of [[Último Guerrero]] when he was the last wrestler in the ring, eliminating Guerrero Negro Jr. to earn his spot in the finals for the following week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediotiempo.com/mas-deportes/lucha-libre/noticias/2013/03/06/taurus-segundo-finalista-de-sangre-nueva-2013|title=Taurus segundo finalista de Sangre Nueva 2013|date=March 6, 2013|accessdate=March 6, 2013|work=Medio Tiempo|language=Spanish}}</ref> The following week, Sobereano Jr. defeated Taurus, two falls to one to win the 2013 ''Sangre Nueva'' tournament.<ref name=SangreNueva2013>{{cite web|url=http://superluchas.net/2013/03/12/soberano-jr-gana-el-torneo-sangre-nueva-2013/|title=Soberano Jr gana el Torneo Sangre Nueva 2013|date=March 12, 2013|accessdate=March 13, 2013|work=SuperLuchas|language=Spanish}}</ref>
