'''''When Angels Wept'''''<ref>{{cite web|last1=League of Chicago Theatres|title=When Angels Wept|url=http://chicagoplays.com/show/prop-thtr/when-angels-wept.html|website=Chicagoplays.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Broadwayworld|title=New Lincoln Theatre Presents WHEN ANGELS WEPT 9/14-10/27|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/chicago/article/New-Lincoln-Theatre-Presents-WHEN-ANGELS-WEPT-914-1027-20130811|website=Broadwayworld.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Hayford|first1=Justin|title=When Angels Wept - Review|url=http://www.chicagoreader.com/chicago/when-angels-wept/Event?oid=8955724|publisher=Chicago Reader}}</ref> by [[Charles Grippo]] is a play about the [[Our Lady of the Angels School fire]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Our Lady of the Angels (OLA) School Fire|title=Our Lady of the Angels (OLA) School Fire, December 1, 1958|url=http://www.olafire.com/|website=Our Lady of the Angels (OLA) School Fire - Official Website}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Secter|first1=Bob|title=Our Lady of Angels School fire|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/nationworld/politics/chi-chicagodays-ladyangelsfire-story-story.html|publisher=Chicago Tribune}}</ref> It had two productions in 2013 by New Lincoln Theatre at the Prop Theatre and City Lit Theatre in [[Chicago|Chicago, Illinois]]. The story is centered on a small group of survivors of the fire and how the tragedy affected their lives until present day.

